1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,333
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:02,733
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:05,933
(Episode 33)

4
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:10,733
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

5
00:00:11,835 --> 00:00:13,021
Team Manager.

6
00:00:28,984 --> 00:00:30,084
How are you feeling today?

7
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:33,446
I'm not even the one presenting,
but my heart is racing.

8
00:00:34,917 --> 00:00:36,017
You can do this, right?

9
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:37,900
I believe you'll do well.

10
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,033
Joy says...

11
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:42,400
you tend to speak a bit fast
when you're nervous.

12
00:00:43,099 --> 00:00:44,700
I think that's the only thing
you need to watch out for.

13
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:48,733
What...

14
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:53,400
Hello, Chairman.

15
00:00:54,869 --> 00:00:57,500
Team Manager Ko, are you fully prepared?

16
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,100
Yes, I'll do my best.

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,600
- Let's go up, Chairman.
- Yes.

18
00:01:08,584 --> 00:01:10,333
Follow me. I have something to say.

19
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:11,700
Yes, sir.

20
00:01:27,021 --> 00:01:29,795
When I first declared this race,

21
00:01:30,557 --> 00:01:32,233
I was worried deep down,

22
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:36,200
but seeing you all do your best
in your own positions...

23
00:01:37,009 --> 00:01:38,076
puts my mind at ease.

24
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:41,333
Of course we should do our best.

25
00:01:42,579 --> 00:01:47,000
Don't think about winning
by bringing the other side down.

26
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:51,413
Think about winning
by coming up with a better answer.

27
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,400
You understand what I mean, right?

28
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:56,753
Yes, I understand.

29
00:01:57,252 --> 00:01:58,252
Yes.

30
00:01:59,488 --> 00:02:01,833
I don't know
who will end up owning this room,

31
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:06,000
but remember,
this position is not inherited.

32
00:02:07,171 --> 00:02:09,500
It's a position that comes...

33
00:02:10,593 --> 00:02:11,660
with responsibility.

34
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,400
(Chairman Ko Kang Su)

35
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:20,200
(Chairman Ko Dae Chi)

36
00:02:26,325 --> 00:02:27,325
Again.

37
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,833
Do it again!

38
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,533
Yes, I'll redo it.

39
00:02:34,747 --> 00:02:38,433
Hey, fire Seo Gwon Sik right away.

40
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:41,233
Fire Mr. Seo?

41
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:44,971
Chairman! Please don't fire me!

42
00:02:45,728 --> 00:02:47,000
I have a family to support.

43
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,483
Chairman, please go easy on me.

44
00:02:48,881 --> 00:02:49,881
- Listen!
- Please show mercy.

45
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:52,400
In Kangsu Group, I am the law.

46
00:02:52,804 --> 00:02:55,271
This is Ko Dae Chi's kingdom!

47
00:02:55,533 --> 00:02:57,900
Kingdom!

48
00:03:02,847 --> 00:03:04,247
Why are you giggling?

49
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:06,400
Did you hear what I said properly?

50
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:08,800
Yes.

51
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:10,833
Of course.

52
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,133
You all may go now.

53
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:15,900
See you later.

54
00:03:16,017 --> 00:03:17,017
- Yes.
- Yes.

55
00:03:26,005 --> 00:03:29,700
I think I finally understand
your deeper intentions, Chairman.

56
00:03:31,001 --> 00:03:32,068
My deeper intentions?

57
00:03:32,949 --> 00:03:36,100
I failed to grasp your deeper plan
to have Min Ho and Gyeol...

58
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:39,300
compete to become the next-next chairman.

59
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,573
Are you saying...

60
00:03:43,341 --> 00:03:45,933
you consider yourself the next chairman?

61
00:03:46,656 --> 00:03:50,200
Have you forgotten
that if you fail to fairly manage...

62
00:03:51,117 --> 00:03:54,200
and supervise them this time,
you'll be out...

63
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,100
of this race?

64
00:03:57,672 --> 00:03:59,141
Yes, understood.

65
00:03:59,771 --> 00:04:02,400
Then I'll see you at the competition.

66
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,400
(Retirement Community Project,
The First Competition)

67
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:17,833
(Kangsu Construction's New Masterpiece)

68
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,433
(A Nature-Friendly Retirement Community
for Your Loved Ones)

69
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,033
(TF Team One)

70
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,533
(TF Team Two)

71
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:29,600
Before we begin the competition,

72
00:04:29,973 --> 00:04:32,080
I will introduce the external judges...

73
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,033
who will be joining us via video today.

74
00:04:37,785 --> 00:04:38,785
Wait a moment.

75
00:04:40,245 --> 00:04:42,433
External judges?

76
00:04:43,445 --> 00:04:44,933
What is this all of a sudden?

77
00:04:45,125 --> 00:04:48,733
They are a panel of professional judges
invited at my request.

78
00:04:52,261 --> 00:04:53,400
Connect them.

79
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:04,200
Hello. I'm architect Yu Yeong Jun.

80
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:07,523
Today, I will be observing
with great interest...

81
00:05:07,523 --> 00:05:09,556
how space can transform human life.

82
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:15,173
I'm Hiroshi Nakamura from
the Japan Aging Society Policy Institute.

83
00:05:15,173 --> 00:05:18,973
I will focus on the care systems
and policies of the retirement community.

84
00:05:20,349 --> 00:05:22,533
My name is Claire Graham,

85
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:25,800
CEO of New York Evergreen Seniors' Town.

86
00:05:27,024 --> 00:05:30,633
The focus of my review
will be on brand strategy...

87
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:32,400
and investment returns.

88
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,233
(A Prestigious Sanctuary
for the Top 0.1 Percent of Seniors)

89
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:42,560
KudoSanctuary.

90
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:46,139
Based on Kangsu Construction's "KS,"

91
00:05:46,693 --> 00:05:48,533
we combined "kudos,"
meaning honor or recognition,

92
00:05:49,131 --> 00:05:52,851
and "sanctuary," meaning refuge,
to create the brand name.

93
00:05:54,579 --> 00:05:57,195
A prestigious and honorable sanctuary...

94
00:05:57,700 --> 00:06:00,243
for the top 0.1 percent of seniors.

95
00:06:01,037 --> 00:06:02,900
Allow me to introduce KudoSanctuary.

96
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,433
(All Units with Terrace and City View,
Premium Finishes and Custom Furniture)

97
00:06:07,433 --> 00:06:08,800
(Top Medical Staff Available 24 Hours,
Private Entertainment Rooms)

98
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:24,100
The biometric data
of seniors residing in KudoSanctuary...

99
00:06:24,373 --> 00:06:26,400
will be monitored by AI 24 hours a day...

100
00:06:26,741 --> 00:06:30,700
to ensure they receive care
from the nation's top medical staff.

101
00:06:37,792 --> 00:06:40,000
We also promise...

102
00:06:40,464 --> 00:06:42,200
the most private environment...

103
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,400
where you can enjoy
high-quality culture and sports.

104
00:06:52,413 --> 00:06:55,200
If I'd been made a judge,

105
00:06:55,928 --> 00:06:57,900
I could've cast my precious vote
for Min Ho.

106
00:06:59,701 --> 00:07:00,701
No.

107
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,900
I have a more important mission than that.

108
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:07,900
Anyway, I must uncover
this family's secret with my own hands...

109
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,000
Wait.

110
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:14,800
Father's precious confidential document...

111
00:07:16,039 --> 00:07:17,039
Could it be?

112
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,800
This darn password, seriously.

113
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,000
(Password)

114
00:07:28,585 --> 00:07:29,585
(Incorrect password. Please try again.)

115
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:30,700
What the...

116
00:07:32,475 --> 00:07:34,733
My goodness, was it really 0000?

117
00:07:37,405 --> 00:07:39,033
"Childish Bunny?" What is this?

118
00:07:43,368 --> 00:07:44,533
What's this?

119
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:48,448
Wait, this photo is of that young lady
from before.

120
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:49,733
Su Jeong!

121
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:51,115
Mother.

122
00:07:54,312 --> 00:07:56,528
What is wrong with you?

123
00:07:57,757 --> 00:07:59,800
Wasn't it enough
snooping through our room?

124
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,500
Now even Gyeol's room?

125
00:08:01,747 --> 00:08:03,120
Snooping?

126
00:08:03,765 --> 00:08:06,333
As the wife
of Kangsu Group's future chairman,

127
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:09,896
I just wanted to see what kind of
retirement community Gyeol's planning...

128
00:08:09,896 --> 00:08:10,896
Come on.

129
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:13,325
All right, Mother. I'll leave.

130
00:08:14,771 --> 00:08:15,771
Mother...

131
00:08:16,307 --> 00:08:19,000
I think Gyeol is dating someone.

132
00:08:19,899 --> 00:08:21,599
- What?
- Look at this.

133
00:08:23,922 --> 00:08:26,835
Look,
it's full of that young lady's photos.

134
00:08:27,448 --> 00:08:30,560
That intern who came
when Father was hospitalized last time.

135
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:33,000
The daughter of Dae Chi's janitor friend.

136
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:39,107
Birds of a feather
really do flock together.

137
00:08:39,107 --> 00:08:40,307
Get out right away.

138
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,500
Okay.

139
00:08:52,155 --> 00:08:54,700
Gyeol's expression has become...

140
00:08:56,101 --> 00:08:57,700
much more relaxed than before.

141
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,933
Thank you, miss.

142
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,300
("Our Happy Home")

143
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,184
Before designing Our Happy Home,

144
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,435
this question came to my mind.

145
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:15,248
Are they truly wrapping up their lives?

146
00:09:15,493 --> 00:09:18,000
Or are they welcoming a new beginning?

147
00:09:23,033 --> 00:09:24,733
This is not a house to end one's life,

148
00:09:25,325 --> 00:09:27,700
but a house that will remain as memories
even after one leaves.

149
00:09:29,427 --> 00:09:30,500
As people age,

150
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:33,633
their range of activity
and social circles shrink.

151
00:09:34,571 --> 00:09:35,700
But humans...

152
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,300
are beings
who must live within relationships.

153
00:09:39,544 --> 00:09:41,400
Ms. Cho, the blueprint.

154
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,600
(Site Plan)

155
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,733
This trail is not just a passageway.

156
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,400
It's an alley.

157
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:53,300
A place where residents
naturally encounter each other,

158
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,500
converse, and take a moment to rest.

159
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,400
In other words,
it is a micro-community road.

160
00:09:58,091 --> 00:10:01,533
Our Happy Home
is thus designed not for living alone,

161
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:04,133
but for living together.

162
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:24,433
Thank you for your valuable time.

163
00:10:25,899 --> 00:10:28,700
- Just get to the point.
- Okay.

164
00:10:34,331 --> 00:10:36,700
- This is for you.
- Excuse me?

165
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:38,685
Please forget all the bad impressions...

166
00:10:38,685 --> 00:10:41,347
you may have had of me
due to various incidents.

167
00:10:42,182 --> 00:10:43,182
This is...

168
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,300
I'm giving this to you as a true fan
of "The ER Witch," so please accept it.

169
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:50,933
All right, then.

170
00:10:52,528 --> 00:10:55,200
Five, four, three,

171
00:10:55,995 --> 00:10:57,925
two, one.

172
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,900
Why isn't she calling me?

173
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,133
(I'll check on the patient!)

174
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,333
(What are the vitals?
Blood pressure, 90 over 60.)

175
00:11:10,755 --> 00:11:11,755
A quarter.

176
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,947
An eighth...

177
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,133
A sixteenth...

178
00:11:16,764 --> 00:11:17,764
Excuse me.

179
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,333
Yes?

180
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:23,528
Did you call me?

181
00:11:25,379 --> 00:11:26,379
Aren't you going to take your bag?

182
00:11:32,115 --> 00:11:34,600
I got lost in thought for a moment
and forgot.

183
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,528
The art style feels fresh.

184
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:41,900
Sorry?

185
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,048
Then does that mean...

186
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,733
you like my drawings?

187
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:51,613
Let me think about it for a few days.

188
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:54,563
You illustrated my novel with such care,

189
00:11:54,874 --> 00:11:56,374
so although it's a bit annoying...

190
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,771
Thank you!

191
00:11:58,260 --> 00:11:59,260
Thank you!

192
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,573
Please take a look at my drawings
and contact me.

193
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:24,133
(Everyone calls me the ER Witch?)

194
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,600
(Thank you.
We will now begin the Q and A session.)

195
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:31,472
If this is carried out
exactly as Team One designed it,

196
00:12:31,472 --> 00:12:34,752
it seems Kangsu Construction's brand value
would also rise.

197
00:12:35,992 --> 00:12:38,493
With twin 30-story towers,

198
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:41,907
it's highly viable
from a profitability standpoint.

199
00:12:42,301 --> 00:12:45,883
Well,
I think Team Two's eco-friendly concept...

200
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,700
isn't bad either.

201
00:12:50,501 --> 00:12:53,152
Claire, what's your take on this?

202
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,933
Mr. Ko Gyeol, I am impressed...

203
00:12:56,933 --> 00:12:58,880
by your intention for the community.

204
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:02,300
But I wonder if you considered profits.

205
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:05,400
Thank you for the good point, Mrs. Claire.

206
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:10,957
But we can't calculate the profitability
without a final budget,

207
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:14,133
so I think it's early to talk about that.

208
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:17,700
I have a question for Team One.

209
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:20,800
I noticed there's no dining facility
in the shared space.

210
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:25,243
Yes.
Instead, meals by Michelin-star chefs...

211
00:13:25,243 --> 00:13:27,899
will be provided via room service.

212
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,300
Team Manager Ko Gyeol,

213
00:13:29,739 --> 00:13:32,035
is there a particular reason
you planned a garden...

214
00:13:32,035 --> 00:13:33,549
focused on vegetable plots
and fruit trees?

215
00:13:33,984 --> 00:13:37,600
Yes. As people get older,
it's hard to go out just to exercise.

216
00:13:37,813 --> 00:13:40,419
But when lettuce grows in the garden
and fruits ripen,

217
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,133
they'll definitely want to come out
and see.

218
00:13:42,971 --> 00:13:46,000
If they need to exercise,
they can just play golf, swim,

219
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:48,033
or go jogging.

220
00:13:50,584 --> 00:13:51,725
Chairman,
would you like to say a few words?

221
00:13:53,763 --> 00:13:55,000
Both teams...

222
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:58,300
have brought out their strengths well.

223
00:13:59,861 --> 00:14:01,933
Do your best until the end.

224
00:14:02,432 --> 00:14:03,933
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

225
00:14:06,477 --> 00:14:08,059
You saw the judges' expressions, right?

226
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,152
I have a feeling our team will win
by a landslide.

227
00:14:11,293 --> 00:14:12,851
Great work, Chief Ko.

228
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:16,432
Was it just me? We all did this together.

229
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,100
Humility is overrated.

230
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:20,300
Please enjoy your moment, Chief Ko.

231
00:14:20,661 --> 00:14:23,552
The results aren't out yet,
so don't jump to conclusions.

232
00:14:23,552 --> 00:14:25,552
By the way, where did Team Two go?

233
00:14:26,384 --> 00:14:27,800
Who knows?
Maybe they're gathered somewhere,

234
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,579
analyzing why they lost today.

235
00:14:32,661 --> 00:14:33,933
Wait a moment.

236
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,389
Why are there only two of you?
Where's Team Manager Ko?

237
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:38,155
I'm not sure.

238
00:14:38,253 --> 00:14:40,933
I just went to the archive room
to return something.

239
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,300
I don't really know either.

240
00:14:42,533 --> 00:14:45,829
Then let's decide on a place
for dinner tonight first.

241
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:48,933
Everyone worked hard,
so regardless of the result,

242
00:14:49,293 --> 00:14:50,833
let's enjoy ourselves tonight.

243
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,900
Chief Ko, there's a place that's trending
on social media these days.

244
00:14:54,088 --> 00:14:55,549
May I recommend it?

245
00:14:55,549 --> 00:14:57,949
Great. Post the link in the group chat.

246
00:14:58,168 --> 00:14:59,968
Everyone else, feel free too.

247
00:15:17,013 --> 00:15:18,317
How did you know I was here?

248
00:15:18,573 --> 00:15:21,440
I just had a feeling
you'd need a WOV right now.

249
00:15:21,871 --> 00:15:22,871
A WOV?

250
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:25,200
A wide-open view.

251
00:15:26,477 --> 00:15:28,300
I've always been curious.

252
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:30,700
Where did you learn to shorten words
however you want?

253
00:15:30,901 --> 00:15:32,900
King Sejong would be upset.

254
00:15:33,373 --> 00:15:34,533
It's not something I learned.

255
00:15:34,971 --> 00:15:37,000
Let's just call it natural talent.

256
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:42,900
Don't be too discouraged.
We don't know the result yet.

257
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:46,300
Discouraged? Do I look discouraged?

258
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:49,519
Of course, I think our team is superior.

259
00:15:50,147 --> 00:15:53,200
But the judges' reactions were a bit off,
right?

260
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,800
Especially regarding profitability.

261
00:15:55,488 --> 00:15:57,043
Isn't that what's bothering you?

262
00:15:57,043 --> 00:15:58,371
No, not at all.

263
00:15:59,109 --> 00:16:00,776
I just want to build a real home
for seniors,

264
00:16:00,776 --> 00:16:03,165
the kind my team and I believe in.

265
00:16:03,484 --> 00:16:04,884
I'm not interested in winning or losing.

266
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:08,433
Still, it would've been nice...

267
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:11,000
if your sincerity reached the judges.

268
00:16:12,825 --> 00:16:13,825
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

269
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:18,500
Trust me. And trust yourself too.

270
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:23,133
Let's do well together
in the second and third rounds.

271
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,000
With you here, I'll do even better.

272
00:16:35,677 --> 00:16:36,677
Sounds good.

273
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:40,633
Let's build a truly great home together.

274
00:16:42,661 --> 00:16:44,347
- What?
- I won.

275
00:16:44,347 --> 00:16:45,780
What's this? So childish.

276
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:00,456
(Grandma's Bindaetteok)

277
00:17:00,456 --> 00:17:02,956
We worked hard for the first round!

278
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:05,833
- Let's have fun!
- Let's have fun!

279
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:06,833
All right.

280
00:17:10,025 --> 00:17:11,425
It's so sweet.

281
00:17:12,256 --> 00:17:13,400
This is nice.

282
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,371
Here's more makgeolli...

283
00:17:16,277 --> 00:17:18,700
Team Manager,
why are you so natural at this?

284
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:19,800
- What?
- Exactly.

285
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,300
Do you work part-time at this restaurant?

286
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:23,000
No, you totally look like a regular here.

287
00:17:23,165 --> 00:17:24,317
He is a regular.

288
00:17:24,944 --> 00:17:26,779
He's been here three times with Eun Ae.

289
00:17:27,033 --> 00:17:29,717
What? Just the two of you?

290
00:17:30,259 --> 00:17:33,149
One of those times
was with me and Manager Seo too.

291
00:17:33,401 --> 00:17:35,568
I've been here about five times before.
You remember me, right?

292
00:17:36,019 --> 00:17:39,821
I don't remember.
You have such an unremarkable face.

293
00:17:39,821 --> 00:17:40,821
No way.

294
00:17:41,037 --> 00:17:43,147
This isn't the kind of face
you forget easily.

295
00:17:43,539 --> 00:17:44,627
All right.

296
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:47,533
Here's your
Dubai chocolate cheese bindaetteok.

297
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:48,533
Take this.

298
00:17:50,059 --> 00:17:52,088
Why am I only finding out today...

299
00:17:52,283 --> 00:17:54,033
that this place is self-service?

300
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,700
I should post this on social media.

301
00:17:57,251 --> 00:17:58,433
Now it's my turn.

302
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,900
- Move.
- Okay.

303
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:01,700
Substitution.

304
00:18:03,072 --> 00:18:06,781
Whatever that is,
it will blow your taste buds away.

305
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:08,033
Get ready...

306
00:18:08,195 --> 00:18:10,733
for Grandma's authentic bindaetteok!

307
00:18:14,752 --> 00:18:16,739
Okay, let's all have a drink together.

308
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:18,033
Cheers!

309
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:19,600
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

310
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:27,157
Team Manager Ko, I was surprised.

311
00:18:27,157 --> 00:18:29,800
How did you come up
with such an ideal retirement community?

312
00:18:30,752 --> 00:18:34,587
I think that's the shared vision...

313
00:18:34,768 --> 00:18:36,500
of Team Manager Ko Gyeol
and Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

314
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:38,443
No. That's just how Ms. Cho Eun Ae is.

315
00:18:38,741 --> 00:18:41,672
Whatever she does,
she throws profitability aside.

316
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:49,100
Chief Ko, Team Manager,
may I make a suggestion?

317
00:18:49,733 --> 00:18:52,987
Since both teams' strategies
were revealed in the first round,

318
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:56,379
how about switching team members
for the second round?

319
00:18:57,065 --> 00:18:58,265
Switch team members?

320
00:18:58,371 --> 00:19:00,100
It's to help develop employees' skills...

321
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:02,433
and give them diverse team experience.

322
00:19:02,837 --> 00:19:06,547
For example,
if we switch the developers...

323
00:19:06,547 --> 00:19:07,700
Ms. Cho Eun Ae and Mr. Han Ji Hun...

324
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:08,885
No, that's not possible.

325
00:19:11,371 --> 00:19:13,900
We're in the middle of developing
the second-round solution...

326
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:16,500
based on the first round,
and now you want to switch team members?

327
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,845
I feel the same way.

328
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:19,633
The Joy system I'm developing...

329
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,627
is tailored
to Team Two's retirement community,

330
00:19:21,627 --> 00:19:25,500
so it would be difficult to apply it
to Team One's retirement community.

331
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,605
I agree as well.

332
00:19:28,475 --> 00:19:32,133
Your intentions are good,
but that would be difficult.

333
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:35,968
I was just offering a suggestion.
Understood.

334
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:39,833
Drink up.

335
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,733
Eat a lot. Enjoy your food.

336
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:43,733
Yes.

337
00:19:43,987 --> 00:19:47,600
Cho Rong, we're out of cooking oil
and low on bean sprouts.

338
00:19:48,233 --> 00:19:49,731
I'll go buy some right away.

339
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:51,229
I can just go
to the mart at the intersection, right?

340
00:19:52,249 --> 00:19:53,249
You're going alone at night?

341
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,033
The cooking oil will be heavy.

342
00:19:56,033 --> 00:19:57,037
I'll go with her.

343
00:19:59,984 --> 00:20:01,033
I should try some.

344
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,033
Nice.

345
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,500
- It doesn't taste sweet.
- It's good.

346
00:20:06,265 --> 00:20:07,265
What?

347
00:20:07,453 --> 00:20:09,400
Mother called you first and asked to meet?

348
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,476
How did she look?

349
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:14,173
Did she seem sick or anything?

350
00:20:14,856 --> 00:20:17,997
Don't worry too much. She looked fine.

351
00:20:19,629 --> 00:20:20,629
That's a relief.

352
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,133
What did she say to you?

353
00:20:23,792 --> 00:20:25,533
There must've been a reason
she wanted to meet.

354
00:20:26,899 --> 00:20:29,653
She asked me
to keep it strictly confidential,

355
00:20:29,949 --> 00:20:31,523
so I can't go into details.

356
00:20:32,261 --> 00:20:34,144
But I feel like...

357
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:38,619
she's made
some kind of different decision.

358
00:20:39,165 --> 00:20:40,600
That makes me a bit uneasy.

359
00:20:41,024 --> 00:20:42,333
What kind of decision?

360
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,909
Be more specific.

361
00:20:48,604 --> 00:20:52,021
Honey, keeping a promise is important,

362
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:54,955
but for our family's peace of mind
and to solve this problem,

363
00:20:55,472 --> 00:20:56,900
can't you tell us everything?

364
00:20:58,833 --> 00:20:59,833
Well...

365
00:21:00,565 --> 00:21:03,500
She said I shouldn't endure everything
for the sake of family,

366
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:06,800
but live only for my own life.

367
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:10,611
Are you saying
she told you to divorce Eun Hyeong?

368
00:21:10,611 --> 00:21:11,611
Cho Eun Nim!

369
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:17,360
What on earth is she thinking?

370
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,800
(Geometric Series Definition)

371
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,200
Come meet me.

372
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:35,192
I need to tell you something, honey.

373
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,700
Tomorrow at 11 a.m.

374
00:21:50,643 --> 00:21:52,453
I know
you've been very considerate of me...

375
00:21:52,757 --> 00:21:54,600
while preparing for this competition.

376
00:21:55,235 --> 00:21:56,500
Thank you so much.

377
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:57,732
Considerate?

378
00:21:57,888 --> 00:21:59,600
I don't remember being considerate.

379
00:22:01,304 --> 00:22:03,272
Are you trying to act all cold
or something?

380
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:05,300
It's not very charming.

381
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,800
I never tried to be charming.

382
00:22:10,573 --> 00:22:12,500
How do you like this neighborhood?
Is it livable?

383
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,493
Of course. I've never left this place,

384
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:17,400
and I never want to leave.

385
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:21,900
This neighborhood is fun
to walk around in.

386
00:22:23,376 --> 00:22:26,533
When you talked about the trails,

387
00:22:26,912 --> 00:22:28,633
it reminded me of the alleys
in my neighborhood.

388
00:22:30,523 --> 00:22:33,033
That's why I enjoyed working on this
even more.

389
00:22:34,816 --> 00:22:38,259
Even if I'm having a rough day elsewhere,
the moment I step into this neighborhood,

390
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,000
I feel at ease somehow.

391
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:43,944
Is that so?

392
00:23:00,877 --> 00:23:01,877
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

393
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:06,400
Trust me. And trust yourself too.

394
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:11,000
Let's do well together
in the second and third rounds.

395
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:15,000
With you here, I'll do even better too.

396
00:23:21,785 --> 00:23:22,785
Sounds good.

397
00:23:23,389 --> 00:23:27,400
Let's build a truly great home together.

398
00:23:44,475 --> 00:23:47,133
You worked really hard
preparing for the competition.

399
00:23:55,835 --> 00:23:57,000
What are you doing this weekend?

400
00:23:58,067 --> 00:24:01,033
Should we meet
and start preparing for the second round?

401
00:24:14,229 --> 00:24:15,763
You were amazing today.

402
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:18,400
Get some good rest this weekend
and see you next week.

403
00:24:20,608 --> 00:24:22,100
Are you going to the office this weekend?

404
00:24:22,704 --> 00:24:24,400
Call me anytime if you need me.

405
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:44,260
- Good night.
- Good night.

406
00:24:44,496 --> 00:24:45,800
- Ms. Cho Eun Ae.
- Team Manager.

407
00:24:54,255 --> 00:24:55,555
Why did you call me here?

408
00:24:57,269 --> 00:24:59,707
This place feels like both my beginning...

409
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,800
and my end.

410
00:25:02,152 --> 00:25:03,800
What do you mean, your end?

411
00:25:06,341 --> 00:25:08,368
Let's go somewhere and talk over a meal.

412
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:10,000
You look worn out.

413
00:25:12,592 --> 00:25:14,091
You've lost weight too.

414
00:25:15,099 --> 00:25:16,171
I'm really sorry.

415
00:25:17,459 --> 00:25:19,900
But you know why I did that.

416
00:25:21,082 --> 00:25:22,082
Also,

417
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:25,200
I'll be working at Kangsu Construction's
secretary's office starting Monday.

418
00:25:25,733 --> 00:25:28,300
I'll put everything back in order now,

419
00:25:29,033 --> 00:25:31,552
so let's go home. Okay, honey?

420
00:25:31,552 --> 00:25:32,856
Did you think
I'd be disappointed in you...

421
00:25:34,813 --> 00:25:38,867
for losing your job
and working as a cleaner?

422
00:25:39,243 --> 00:25:40,981
No. Never.

423
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:46,533
I just didn't like it.

424
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,900
Making you suffer again...

425
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:52,400
after making you suffer your whole life.

426
00:25:55,573 --> 00:25:57,893
If you had been honest from the beginning,

427
00:25:59,184 --> 00:26:02,851
I would've rolled up my sleeves
and cleaned with you.

428
00:26:03,976 --> 00:26:07,003
Losing a job can happen.

429
00:26:08,072 --> 00:26:09,300
Why would I be disappointed?

430
00:26:10,333 --> 00:26:11,333
You're right.

431
00:26:12,368 --> 00:26:15,100
I don't understand myself either.

432
00:26:16,904 --> 00:26:19,600
I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

433
00:26:21,157 --> 00:26:24,187
So that's all I was to you.

434
00:26:26,523 --> 00:26:27,600
From now on,

435
00:26:28,952 --> 00:26:31,024
I won't live such a hollow life anymore.

436
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:36,100
What's this?

437
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,900
(Application for Confirmation
of Intent to Divorce by Mutual Agreement)

438
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:44,792
- Honey.
- I've already stamped mine,

439
00:26:44,792 --> 00:26:46,400
so you just need to stamp yours.

440
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:50,216
Let's meet in front of the courthouse
on Monday.

441
00:26:50,933 --> 00:26:51,933
I'll get going.

442
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:56,200
What's with you, Kang Yeon Ja? Divorce?

443
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:58,200
How can we get divorced?

444
00:27:03,033 --> 00:27:05,300
Let me go, please.

445
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,533
It's late,
but I want to truly live my life now.

446
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:19,200
(Application for Confirmation
of Intent to Divorce by Mutual Agreement)

447
00:27:30,484 --> 00:27:31,484
Honey!

448
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:50,933
Honey! Watch out!

449
00:28:03,825 --> 00:28:04,825
Honey!

450
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,600
(Our Happy Days)

451
00:28:12,869 --> 00:28:14,700
Good to have you back, Mom.

452
00:28:14,833 --> 00:28:16,152
Thank you for coming back.

453
00:28:16,152 --> 00:28:19,227
Right, the day after tomorrow
is Gyeol's father's memorial day.

454
00:28:19,227 --> 00:28:21,633
How long are we going to keep holding
that memorial at our house?

455
00:28:21,633 --> 00:28:23,300
My love for you...

456
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:24,600
hasn't changed at all since then.

457
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:27,619
I don't have the capacity
to love or accept anyone.

458
00:28:27,619 --> 00:28:28,856
What about Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

459
00:28:28,856 --> 00:28:31,833
Do you feel the same way about her
as you do about me?

460
00:28:32,033 --> 00:28:33,700
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
